						<summary>

						<p>On a stone in front of the Vīrabhadrasvāmi temple situated in survey No. 543, to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>1831 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1753, Khara, Śrāvaṇa, śu. 5, Mamdavāra (Saturday) corresponding to 1831 A.D., August 12, Friday f.d.t. °80.</p>						

						<p>Refers to the sevice <hi rend="italic">(sēva)</hi> by a woman Pullaṁmma, wife of Pullabattu, Pullabattu is described as the son of Vīrabattu and the grandson Vīrabattu of Vēlpucharla.</p>						

						</summary>
